comment.undefined: An object containing the information about a pinned item with easily serializable structure.
Object containing the information about legacy Revit addins managed by BuroHappold_Revit_Toolkit.
Object containing the information about BuroHappold_Revit_Toolkit dockable pane.
An interface that indicates that the implementing class is a application service settings class meant to be managed by BuroHappold_Revit_Toolkit.
An interface that indicates that the implementing class is a standard settings class meant to be managed by BuroHappold_Revit_Toolkit.
Object containing the information about Revit ribbon items managed by BuroHappold_Revit_Toolkit.
An object being a part of an IScenario. It carries information about a filter to be checked against one of the input elements when evaluating applicability of the entire scenario.

A general concept of scenario: an object, against which a set of Revit elements is checked.
Each implementation of IScenario has a method ExecuteAction: if the set of Revit elements passes the filters of the scenario, ExecuteAction is called on them.
Single element specific implementation of IScenario. See the description of the latter for more details.
Two element specific implementation of IScenario. See the description of the latter for more details.
Base type for all Revit log items.
Top interface for all logs generated by Revit methods.
Top interface for all log items generated by Revit methods.
Revit method log recommended in standard cases.
Attribute storing the information about the method to be represented as a ribbon ComboBox.
Attribute indicating that the target method will manage Revit transactions by itself.
Attribute storing tags to group methods together.
Attribute storing the information about the method to be represented as a ribbon SplitButton.

Attribute for enabling or disabling a specific ribbon button. Set to 'true' to force enable the method on Revit ribbon, and 'false' to force disable it. Without this attribute, the method will be automatically exposed if it passes IsBHoMRevitCompliant check.
Attribute for the file name of a ribbon button icon. Image specification: PNG format, 32x32 pixels, 32 bit, 96 dpi.
Attribute for display name of the ribbon button linked to the given method.
Attribute for a Revit ribbon panel name to which the method will be added by default.
Attribute for a Revit ribbon tab name to which the method will be added by default.
Attribute for a ribbon button tool tip that appears when the mouse pointer hovers over a ribbon button.
Attribute for the file name of a ribbon tool tip image. Image specification: PNG format.
Fragment containing the information about the Revit element that hosts the Revit element correspondent to the BHoM object that carries this.
Toolkit Settings that need to be saved permanently.
IRequest containing the information about the filter that a given Revit element needs to pass in order to be applicable to the scenario.
